gory\":\"functionality\",\"title\":\"Real-time anomaly detection compliance engine\",\"description\":\"Build a streaming analysis layer on top of the audit event buffer that applies statistical and rule-based anomaly detection before events hit disk. Detect burst key derivations, credential access from new IPs, off-hours admin actions, or privilege escalation sequences. Auto-generate SOC2/GDPR compliance reports from audit data. First sprint: implement a sliding-window rate detector on audit actions per tenant that emits warnings via pino when thresholds are exceeded.\",\"reasoning\":\"Currently the audit log is write-and-forget � nobody looks at it until an incident. Proactive anomaly detection turns audit from a post-mortem record into a live security sensor. Auto-generated compliance reports eliminate weeks of manual audit preparation.\",\"status\":\"pending\",\"user_feedback\":null,\"user_pattern\":0,\"effort\":8,\"impact\":9,\"implemented_at\":null,\"created_at\":\"2026-03-18T11:46:04.630Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-18T11:46:04.630Z\",\"requirement_id\":null,\"goal_id\":null,\"risk\":6,\"provider\":null,\"model\":null,\"detailed\":0}}","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
[2026-03-18T11:46:09.441Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_012YE1WyPQLYfJsK28UzBDTt","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01EshVhsumkTDuvetcugQGv2","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"SCAN_ID=\"593ffec7-d930-43c2-81df-a6fb75c2e9b7\"\nPROJECT_ID=\"c6fd0474-19f1-4223-b6a9-752077c51d3d\"\n\n# Idea 3: Full event-sourced time-travel system replay\ncurl -s -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/ideas \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d \"{\n    \\\"scan_id\\\": \\\"$SCAN_ID\\\",\n    \\\"project_id\\\": \\\"$PROJECT_ID\\\",\n    \\\"scan_type\\\": \\\"moonshot_architect\\\",\n    \\\"category\\\": \\\"functionality\\\",\n    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Full event-sourced time-travel system replay\\\",\n    \\\"description\\\": \\\"Evolve the audit log into a complete event-sourcing backbone capturing every state mutation (tenant CRUD, key rotation, OAuth lifecycle, worker assignments, execution dispatch) with enough context to deterministically replay system state at any timestamp. Build a replay engine and CLI command for point-in-time state reconstruction. First sprint: enrich AuditEntry detail with structured before/after snapshots for tenant DB mutations and add a causal timeline query endpoint.\\\",\n    \\\"reasoning\\\": \\\"When incidents happen, operators piece together what happened from scattered logs. A replayable audit trail means any incident can be reconstructed in minutes, not days. This is the holy grail of observability — not just knowing what happened, but seeing the exact system state at the moment it happened.\\\",\n    \\\"effort\\\": 9,\n    \\\"impact\\\": 8,\n    \\\"risk\\\": 7\n  }\"","description":"Save idea 3"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1246,"cache_read_input_tokens":50582,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1246},"output_